<p lang="en">
    Public authorities are obliged to make websites and mobile applications accessible in accordance with Directive (EU)
    2016/2102 of the European Parliament and the Council. The following accessibility statement documents the implementation
    status of this website in accordance with the &nbsp;<a href="http://gesetze-bayern.de/Content/Document/BayBGG/true">applicable
    legislation</a>.&nbsp;
</p>
<p>
    This accessibility statement belongs to the following website(s):
    <strong>&nbsp;<a href="{{ wisski_url }}">{{ wisski_url }}</a></strong></strong>
</p>


<h2>Compliance status</h2>


    {% if status == 'Completely compliant' %}
        <div class="alert alert-secondary" role="alert">
            <p lang="en">{{ status }}: The content is fully compliant with the accessibility standard without exceptions</p>
        </div>
    {% endif %}

    {% if status == 'Partially compliant' %}
        <div class="alert alert-warning>
            <p lang="en">{{ status }}: Some parts of the content are not fully compliant with the accessibility standard</p>
        </div>
    {% endif %}

    <p lang="en">
        <strong>Methodology:</strong> {{ methodology_en }}
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
        <strong>Date of Creation:</strong> {{ creation_date }}
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
        <strong>Last Revision:</strong> {{ last_revis_date }}
    </p>
    {% if report_url %}
        <p lang="en">
            <strong>Report:</strong> <a href="{{ report_url }}">{{ report_url }}</a>
        </p>
    {% endif %}
    <p lang="en">
        &nbsp;
    </p>


<h2>Known accessibility issues</h2>

    <p lang="en">
        Enumeration and explanation of problems with the implementation of accessibility standards with this application:
    </p>



<h3>Content that is not barrier-free</h3>
    {% if known_issues %}
        <p lang="en">
            <ul>
                {% for issue in issues_array_en %}
                    <li>{{ issue }}</li>
                {% endfor %}
            </ul>
        </p>

        {% if statement_array_de %}
            <h3>Explanatory statement</h3>
            <p lang="en">
                <ul>
                    {% for statement in statement_array_en %}
                        <li>{{ statement }}</li>
                    {% endfor %}
                </ul>
            </p>
    {% endif %}


    {% if alternatives_en %}
        <h3>Alternative access routes</h3>
            <p lang="en">
                <ul>
                    {% for alternative in alternatives_array_en %}
                        <li>{{ alternative }}</li>
                    {% endfor %}
                </ul>
    {% endif %}

{% else %}
        <p>
            All contents are accessible.
        </p>
    {% endif %}

<h3>Help and contact in case of problems</h3>

    <p lang="en">
        In case you encounter shortcomings in meeting accessibility requirements or information for which a barrier-free presentation
        is not mandatory, you may request a barrier-free version. To do so, please direct your queries to the following contacts.
    </p>

    <h4>Contact person</h4>

        <p lang="en">
            <a href="{{ pub_inst_url }}">{{ pub_institute_en }}</a> <br />
            {{ pub_name }}<br />
            {{ pub_address }}<br />
            {{ pub_plz }} - {{ pub_city_en }}<br />
            <a href="mailto:{{ pub_email }}">{{ pub_email }}</a><br />
        </p>
        <p lang="en">
            <a href="{{ sup_url }}">{{ sup_institute_en }} </a> <br />
            {{ sup_address }}<br />
            {{ sup_plz }} - {{ sup_city_en }}<br />
            <a href="mailto:{{ sup_email }}">{{ sup_email }}</a>
        </p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>


